{"word":"ἐκφύω","slug":"ἐκφύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκφύω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ύσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to generate from</i> another, <i>to beget</i>, of the male, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of the female, <i>to bear</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: also, <i>to produce a plant</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> and aor2 <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a>, <i>to be born from</i> another, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>λάλημα ἐκπεφυκός</el> a tattler <i>by nature</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}